Report_Text: Donor was very interested in our cause and asked many questions. However, they mentioned they recently lost their job and cannot commit to anything right now.
The donor seemed disinterested and kept checking their phone. But at the end, they wrote a check for $500.
Had a long conversation about the organization's mission. Donor was very engaged and asked for more information. Will follow up next week.
Donor was polite but clearly not interested. They said they support other charities and cannot help us at this time.
The call went to voicemail. Left a detailed message about our campaign. No response after 3 attempts.
Met the donor at a charity event. They were friendly and asked about our programs. Exchanged business cards.
Donor requested to be removed from our mailing list. They were polite but firm about not wanting future contact.
